About a hundred of civilians have been killed in airstrikes in Central Mali, local media reported late Monday. The strikes took place in the Bounti village of Mali’s Mopti region on Sunday night, Adama Griaba, the mayor of the locality, told local radio station Studio Tamani. Eye witnesses said the death toll might be higher, according to Griaba. ABUJA DOCTOR REVEALS HOW MOST NIGERIA MEN ARE NOW OVERCOMING TERRIBLE BEDROOM PERFORMANCE DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. DON'T BE A VICTIM! He said the airstrikes were carried out at night by an unidentified helicopter, without giving further details. The motive of the incident currently remains unknown and the wounded have been transported to the health district of Douentza. South Africa’s COVID-19 Death Toll Crosses 30,000 Elite Sports To Continue In England In Spite Of National Lockdown No official statement from the government has been received so far. (SOURCE: Anadolu Agency) SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION